  <text>
     <body>
     <div type="poem">
   <pb facs="2"/>
   <head>Author ad Librum</head>
   <l>OLd wiues and fooles haue faith, the <hi>Cricquets</hi> song</l>
   <l>In the warm'd chimney portends deathere long</l>
   <l>My creede holds no such thing. If <hi>Cricquets</hi> sing,</l>
   <l>I rather doubt the'oreheated brickes may bring</l>
   <l>Some danger to my house when these I heare,</l>
   <l>(If any thing) I onely fire do feare:</l>
   <l>But many things (poore Booke) I iustly feare,</l>
   <l>When <hi>Critiques</hi> descants on thy lines I heare.</l>
   <div type="poem">
      <head>Libri ad Authorem responsio.</head>
      <l>Feare no true <hi>Critique;</hi> all that know you, know</l>
      <l>What loue and honor to such men you owe:</l>
      <l>And men of that high name, will neuer throw</l>
      <l>Their censures on an argument so low.</l>
      <l>These I not feare; but I do doubt them though,</l>
      <l>Who would from fooles Censorious <hi>Critiques</hi> grow.</l>
   </div>
   <closer>
      <signed>T. N</signed>
   </closer>
</div>
